usage: flet [-h] [--version]
            {create,run,build,debug,pack,publish,serve,emulators,devices,doctor}
            ...

positional arguments:
  {create,run,build,debug,pack,publish,serve,emulators,devices,doctor}
    create              Create a new Flet project using a predefined template.
                        It sets up the initial directory structure, metadata,
                        and required files to help you get started quickly.
    run                 Run a Flet application in hot reload mode.
    build               Build a Flet Python app into a platform-specific
                        executable or installable bundle. It supports building
                        for desktop (macOS, Linux, Windows), web, Android
                        (APK/AAB), and iOS (IPA and simulator .app), with a
                        wide range of customization options for metadata,
                        assets, splash screens, and signing. Detailed guide
                        with usage examples: https://flet.dev/docs/publish
    debug               Run a Flet Python app in debug mode on a specified
                        platform (desktop, web, mobile).
    pack                Package a Flet application into a standalone desktop
                        executable or app bundle using PyInstaller.
    publish             Compile and package a Flet app as a standalone static
                        web application.
    serve               Serve static files from a directory with a lightweight
                        web server, optionally adding WebAssembly-related
                        headers for Flet web apps.
    emulators           List, create, and launch available emulators.
    devices             List all connected iOS and Android devices.
    doctor              Get information about the system and environment
                        setup.

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --version, -V         show program's version number and exit
